The errors you see are normal compile errors and they come from one simple issue:


Your Role entity does not have a constructor, but in DataInitializer you are calling:


new Role(null, "ROLE_USER")


Java therefore shows:


Expected no arguments but found 2


So we just need to add constructors to the Role entity.



1️⃣ Fix Role.java


Update the file to this complete version.


package com.gateway.authservice.entity;

import jakarta.persistence.*;

@Entity
@Table(name = "roles")
public class Role {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private Long id;

    private String name;

    // 🔹 Default constructor (required by JPA)
    public Role() {
    }

    // 🔹 Constructor used by DataInitializer
    public Role(Long id, String name) {
        this.id = id;
        this.name = name;
    }

    public Long getId() {
        return id;
    }

    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }

    public void setId(Long id) {
        this.id = id;
    }

    public void setName(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }
}


This fixes:


Expected no arguments but found 2



